      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "There is a strong consensus among climate scientists that reducing vehicle miles traveled is absolutely critical for urban sustainability. Congestion pricing is one of the most direct and effective mechanisms to achieve that reduction by incentivizing people to use transit or shift travel times. While some skeptics question the exact magnitude of the environmental impact, the fundamental premise that pricing driving behavior is necessary for meeting climate goals is widely accepted by experts.",
      "source": "target",
