      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The argument that congestion pricing is regressive is a major, persistent critique, and it highlights the need for robust policy design. To counter this, successful implementations must couple the pricing scheme with significant, tangible investments in affordable transit options. If the revenue generated is not directly reinvested into making public transport accessible and affordable for all income levels, then the policy risks becoming an unfair tax on the working poor.",
